    <Object Type="Vector.CANalyzer.Panels.Design.StaticTextControl, Vector.CANalyzer.Panels.CommonControls, Version=18.0.150.0, Culture=neutral, PublicKeyToken=null" Name="StaticTextControl3" ControlName="Static Text 2">
      <Property Name="Name">StaticTextControl3</Property>
      <Property Name="Size">406, 149</Property>
      <Property Name="Location">57, 28</Property>
      <Property Name="BackColor">White</Property>
      <Property Name="Font">Microsoft Sans Serif, 9pt</Property>
      <Property Name="Text">On measurement start the node 'EMS' will perform the address claiming and then it begins transmitting the EEC1 message.

If the TX signals are changed in CANoe, the J1939 Interaction Layer will use the updated values when the parameter group is sent. TX signals can be change in panels, 'Change value'-dialog, Signal Generators, Visual Sequences, CAPL and test nodes.

EEC1 is configured for cyclic transmission, so it will send the the signal EngSpeed every second.
ET1 is configured to send the parameter group when the signal EngCoolantTemp is changed.</Property>
    </Object>
